Apollo Global Management, LLC C (NYSE:APO) Experiences Lighter than Average Trading Volume 












































 Finance DailyDaily markets, commodities, personal finance and economic newsApollo Global Management, LLC C (NYSE:APO) Experiences Lighter than Average Trading Volume
July 26, 2017 By Ted Blackburn Tweet
        Advertisement



Trading volume for Apollo Global Management, LLC C was 16K on Wednesday.  Volume was down 97.51% under the stocks average daily volume. 
 Here is the rundown on market activity for Apollo Global Management, LLC C (NYSE:APO).   Marc J. Rowan, Senior Managing Director sold $28,071,306 worth of shares at a price of $26.45 on Thu the 4th. That brings the Senior Managing Director’s holdings to $0 as reported to the SEC.
 Here are a few other firms who have also updated their positions.   As of the end of the quarter Morgan Stanley had disposed of  a total of 1,329,519 shares trimming its stake by 17.1%. The value in dollars went from $150,761,000 to $157,051,000 a change of $6,290,000 quarter to quarter. Goldman Sachs Group Inc trimmed its position by selling 5,673,993 shares a decrease of 95.9% in the quarter. Goldman Sachs Group Inc owns 240,000 shares valued at $5,837,000. The total value of its holdings decreased 94.9%.
 Hightower Advisors, LLC added to its ownership by buying 549 shares an increase of 0.8%. Hightower Advisors, LLC currently owns 68,399 shares with a value of $1,666,000. The value of the position overall is up by 26.7%. As of quarter end Capital World Investors had bought 1,087,687 shares growing its holdings by 19.8%. The value of the investment in APO increased from $106,087,000 to $159,719,000 a change of 50.6% for the reporting period.
  October 11 investment analysts at Jefferies maintained a company rating of “Buy” and raised the price expectation from $20.00 to $23.00. On July 11 Keefe Bruyette & Woods left the company rating at “Market Perform” but lowered the price target  to $18.00 from $27.00.        Advertisement






 On March 22 Jefferies left the stock rating at “Buy” but raised the price expectation from $17.00 to $20.00. March 11 investment analysts at Deutsche Bank made no change to the stock rating of “Hold” and moved up the price target  to $15.00 from $14.00.
 February 9 investment analysts at Deutsche Bank kept the company rating at “Hold” but moved down the price target  to $12.00 from $13.00. January 13 investment analysts at Keefe Bruyette & Woods held the stock rating at “Market Perform” and lowered the price target  to $18.00 from $22.00.
 The company is so far trading up by 0.39 percent from yesterday’s close.  The company announced a dividend which was paid on Wednesday May 31st, 2017.  The dividend payment was $0.490 per share for the quarter or $1.96 on an annualized basis.  This dividend amount represented a yeild of $7.02.  The ex-dividend date was Wednesday the 17th of May 2017. 
 Shares are trading at $28.11 barely above $27.17, the 50 day moving average and a tad above the 200 day moving average of $24.87.  The 50 day moving average was up $0.94 or +3.47% and the 200 day average was up $3.24. 
 Apollo Global Management, LLC C’s P/E ratio is 9.24 and market capitalization is 5.37B.  As of the latest earnings report the EPS was $3.04 and is expected to be $2.47 for the current year with 191,001,000 shares presently outstanding.  Next quarter’s EPS is forecasted to be $0.56 and the next full year EPS is projected to be $2.80. 
 Apollo Global Management, LLC (Apollo), launched on July 3, 2007, is an alternative investment manager in private equity, credit and real estate. The Company raises, invests and manages funds on behalf of pension, endowment and sovereign wealth funds, as well as other institutional and individual investors. The Business’s segments include private equity, credit and real estate. The private equity segment invests in control equity and related debt instruments, convertible securities and distressed debt investments. The credit segment invests in non-control corporate and structured debt instruments, including performing, stressed and distressed investments across the capital structure. The real estate segment invests in real estate equity for the acquisition and recapitalization of real estate assets, portfolios, platforms and operating companies, and real estate debt, including first mortgage and mezzanine loans, preferred equity and commercial mortgage backed securities..
