Apollo Global Management (AGM) LLC is an investment management company that provides alternative solutions to global customers. Specifically, the company invests in private equity and capital real estate markets.  Apollo holdings include McGraw-Hill's Education division, Hostess Brands, LLC, Oceania Cruises,… MoreApollo Global Management (AGM) LLC is an investment management company that provides alternative solutions to global customers. Specifically, the company invests in private equity and capital real estate markets.  Apollo holdings include McGraw-Hill's Education division, Hostess Brands, LLC, Oceania Cruises, Regent Seven Seas Cruises, and CEC Entertainment.

This profile concentrates on the company's US operations.
• Apollo completed its acquisition of Presidio, Inc. in February, 2015.  Presidio continues to operate as an independent subsidiary of Apollo.

At investment management company Apollo Management, LLC, the US, information technology department oversees business solution delivery throughout all global company… More• Apollo completed its acquisition of Presidio, Inc. in February, 2015.  Presidio continues to operate as an independent subsidiary of Apollo.

At investment management company Apollo Management, LLC, the US, information technology department oversees business solution delivery throughout all global company offices.

The IT department is divided into the following core groups: telecommunications, information security, and business applications. The company relies primarily on Hyperion and Oracle Databases for business intelligence purposes. Staff members also support customer relationship management using Sage SalesLogix. 

The Manager of Global Data Centers & Infrastructure Operations oversees data center operations and infrastructure support services.

The IT department at Apollo also makes decisions for the company's subsidiary, Stone Tower Capital.





